      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "15 to 25 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, has fallen since Monday. As a consequence of a strong wind from variable directions, wind slabs formed. <br/> <br/> These are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack above approximately 2000 m. Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack on west, north and east facing slopes. This applies in particular above approximately 2000 m. <br/> <br/> Steep sunny slopes: Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack."
      },
